{
  "name": "RPlog_A_Visit_from_Lando",
  "title": "Lando's Warning on Yavin 4",
  "summary": "Lando Calrissian's opulent yacht Lady Luck descends onto the abandoned Remote Landing Pad on Yavin 4, where the Jedi Jessalyn Valios sits alone tinkering with engine parts beside the freighter Uwannabuyim. Lando greets her with his customary charm and flirtation, putting the uneasy Jessalyn off balance, until Talon Karrde's employee Drew Carvallo arrives with shopping bags and declines an invitation to stay before heading off on errands. Left alone with Jessalyn, Lando steers past the banter to his real purpose: he distrusts Karrde and is troubled that Luke brought the smuggler-chief into their affairs without consulting him. Jessalyn recounts her rescue from Valak's stasis imprisonment by Simon, Mira, and Orson Tighe, and the destruction the Empire wrought on Karrde's holdings, while Lando, uncharacteristically raw, opens up about old wounds and his belief that Karrde makes every choice by the bottom line. He urges her to keep a close eye on Karrde and to call him if she ever needs anything, then makes a flustered, ungraceful retreat back toward the jungle, tossing off a final roguish promise that she can count on him.",
